"title": "5218: authority, in the home",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5218",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The exercise of God-given authority within the husband-wife and parent-child relationships.</p>\n<h2>A husband is given headship over his wife</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:23\">EPH 5:23</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The basis for this headship</h2>\n<h3>God's headship over Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:3\">1CO 11:3</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's headship over the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:23\">EPH 5:23</a></strong></p>\n<h3>God's order of creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:8-1Cor11:9\">1CO 11:8–11:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:20-Gen2:22\">GEN 2:20–2:22</a></p>\n<h2>This headship has been affected by the fall</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:16\">GEN 3:16</a></strong></p>\n<h2>How this headship is to be exercised</h2>\n<h3>Lovingly and sacrificially</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:25\">EPH 5:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:28\">EPH 5:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:33\">EPH 5:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:19\">COL 3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:7\">1PE 3:7</a></p>\n<h3>As Jesus Christ rules as head of the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:25-Eph5:29\">EPH 5:25–5:29</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Regarding his wife as part of himself</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:28-Eph5:29\">EPH 5:28–5:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:7\">1PE 3:7</a></p>\n<h2>Christian wives are to submit to their husbands</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:22\">EPH 5:22</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:18\">COL 3:18</a></p>\n<h3>They are to follow the example of the submission of the church to Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:24\">EPH 5:24</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Fathers are heads of their families</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:19\">GEN 18:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:2\">GEN 35:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:15\">JOS 24:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:4\">EPH 6:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:4\">1TI 3:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:12\">1TI 3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:6\">TIT 1:6</a></p>\n<h2>Fathers' authority is to be exercised reasonably</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:4\">EPH 6:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:21\">COL 3:21</a></p>\n<h2>The response of children to parental authority</h2>\n<h3>Obedience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:1\">EPH 6:1</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:20\">COL 3:20</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:20\">PRO 6:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:22\">PRO 23:22</a></p>\n<h3>Respect</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:2-Eph6:3\">EPH 6:2–6:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:16\">DEU 5:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:12\">EXO 20:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:15\">EXO 21:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:17\">EXO 21:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:16\">DEU 27:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:26\">PRO 19:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:20\">PRO 20:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:19\">MAT 19:19</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:19\">MRK 10:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:20\">LUK 18:20</a></p>\n<h2>Kinds of authority within the family</h2>\n<h3>Authority to discipline</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:18\">PRO 19:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:13\">PRO 23:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:17\">PRO 29:17</a></p>\n<h3>Authority to teach</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:8\">PRO 1:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:1\">PRO 3:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:1\">PRO 13:1</a></p>\n<h3>Authority to command</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:20\">COL 3:20</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:1\">EPH 6:1</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:20-Prov6:23\">PRO 6:20–6:23</a></p>",
